				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hate pop ups as Im sure just about everyone else does but I understand its a necessary evil when using a free site and have no real problem with them except for in one instance.
<br />

<br />
 Where I hate it is when I visit a website and a program is downloaded onto my computer WITHOUT my consent that adds a pop up generating program to where anytime my computer is on will periodically display pop ups whether Im cruising the web or not (I have a cable modem). I had one even that when I uninstalled it asked why I was uninstalling the program. Im thinking duh maybe its because I never asked for you shitty program and I could see no reason anyone would want a program like that on their computer. 
<br />
 
<br />
 Honestly I think that kindof garbage should be illegal I can deal with straight popups but when its a forced prgram that I never wanted thats where I draw the line and anytime I visit a site that allows that type of immoral advertising I never ever visit it again.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
